<title>UK: Northern Electric details board changes.</title>
<headline>Northern Electric details board changes.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Northern Electric Plc said on Tuesday that David Sokol has been appointed chairman and chief executive following its takeover by CE Electric.</p>
<p>Sokol, who is chairman and chief executive officer of CalEnergy Company, CE Energy's parent, takes over from David Morris who joins the CalEnergy Company board.</p>
<p>Tony Hadfield has retired as chief executive but will continue in a consultancy capacity.</p>
<p>Northern said that finance director, John Edwards and commercial director, Ron Dixon will remain as members of the Northern board in their present roles for the time being.</p>
